Developing tree structure using json and jquery:
=========================================

 in eclipse take one static web project and copy the required js ,css .develop the html and json files like bellow.

keep ths demo.json in webcontent.
in this example iam using jquery 1.4 version(jquery.js)

one.html:
=========
<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>


<title>Tree Viewer</title>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/jquery.treeview.css" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/screen.css" />

<script type="text/javascript" src="js/jquery.js"></script>

<!-- <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.4.3/jquery.min.js"></script> -->

<script src="js/jquery.treeview.js" type="text/javascript"></script>

<script src="js/jquery.treeview.async.js" type="text/javascript"></script>

<!--<script src="js/jquery.livequery.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>-->

<script src="js/jQueryRotateCompressed.2.1.js" type="text/javascript"></script>

<script src="js/jquery.jsontreeviewer.js" type="text/javascript"></script>


<script type="text/javascript">
  $(function() {
	alert('1');
		JSONTREEVIEWER.init();
		alert('2');
		JSONTREEVIEWER.processJSONTree('demo.json');
		alert('3');
	});
</script>
</head>
<body>

	<div id="options-wrap" style="display: none;">

		<form id="form2" action="" method="post">
			<input type="checkbox" id="hierarchy_chk" name="hierarchy_chk"
				title="" checked /> <br /> <input type="text" id="pathdelim_chk"
				value="." />
		</form>
	</div>

	<ul id="browser" class="filetree treeview-famfamfam"></ul>

</body>
</html>

demo.json:
===============
{
	"Hotels":["Domestic","International"],
	"Flights":["Domestic","International"],
	"Holidays":["With in India","Out of India","London","Australia"]
}




importent:
==========
$(function() {

		JSONTREEVIEWER.init();
		
		JSONTREEVIEWER.processJSONTree('demo.json');
		
	});


the above two line impartent.here JSONTREEVIEWER. is predefined class in jquery.jsontreeviewer.js.

==================

	<div id="options-wrap" style="display: none;">

		<form id="form2" action="" method="post">
			<input type="checkbox" id="hierarchy_chk" name="hierarchy_chk"
				title="" checked /> <br /> <input type="text" id="pathdelim_chk"
				value="." />
		</form>
	</div>

	<ul id="browser" class="filetree treeview-famfamfam"></ul>


the bout few lines are predefined json tree online example code.dnot change.


downloading the required .js and css file from the bellow links:
=======================================================
